## Handling Incomplete Data - YOU MUST STILL DELIVER

Even if research is incomplete, **ALWAYS produce the full report**:

| Scenario | What To Do |
|----------|------------|
| Draft section missing | Synthesize from raw notes for that topic |
| Notes sparse for a topic | Use available data + note "Limited data available" |
| Numbers not calculated | Provide qualitative assessment + ranges |
| Competitor data incomplete | Profile available competitors, note gaps |
| No data at all for section | Write "Data Not Available" section with explanation, but STILL include it |

